{
  "text": "Although the leaves, which have fewer identified compounds than seeds, possess the highest antioxidant activity in the in vitro antioxidant assays, this bioactivity may be accounted to the unidentified compounds as depicted by a large quantity of peaks in the chromatograms. The differences in the antioxidant capacities of the extracts could also be attributed to the qualitative variability in compounds present between the plant parts [CITATION_1] . Thus, it is recommended to further ",
